schneier@chinet.chinet.com (Bruce Schneier) writes:

>Can anyone help me with information about ISO/IEC 9979.  Supposedly the
>standard sets up a registry of cryptographic algorithms.

>If anyone can point me to a copy of the standard, I would also appreciate it.

The full name of this Standard is:

ISO/IEC 9979:1991
Information technology -- Procedures for the registration
of cryptographic algorithms

The registration authority for it is according to the 1994 ISO Catalogue:

c/o The National Computing Centre Ltd.
Oxford Road
Manchester M1 7ED
United Kingdom

TP +44 61 228 63 33
TF +44 61 228 25 79
TX 66 89 62 nccman g

You can order all ISO standards from ISO central secretariat in Geneva:

   e-mail    sales@isocs.iso.ch
   phone     +41 22 749 01 11

You can also get it from ANSI, but probably more expensive and only
a xerox copy.

More information about international standards is collected in the
'Standards FAQ' in news.answers or on any FAQ server (or ftp.uni-erlangen.de
pub/doc/ISO/std-faq).

Hope this helped ...

Markus

